article.description: Franck Kamgain registered 16 points and six rebounds as Kansas City beat California Baptist 67-57 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Kamgain lifts Kansas City over California Baptist 67-57
article.linkText: Kamgain lifts Kansas City over California Baptist 67-57
article.story: RIVERSIDE, Calif. -- Franck Kamgain registered 16 points and six rebounds as Kansas City beat California Baptist 67-57 on Saturday night. Brandon McKissic had 13 points for Kansas City (10-11, 3-4 Western Athletic Conference), which ended its four-game losing streak. Jordan Giles added 11 points and three blocks. Josiah Allick had nine rebounds. Ferron Flavors Jr. had 19 points for the Lancers (14-6, 4-2), whose four-game win streak was snapped. Milan Acquaah added 14 points. Zach Pirog had 12 points. Kansas City plays Crowley's Ridge College at home on Monday. California Baptist plays Utah Valley on the road on Wednesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
